Great staff

They are charging a $5 delivery fee. None of which goes to the driver. I called and spoke with the local manager, Mario. He explained that the delivery drivers are employees of Jett's who make less than minimum wage. Not a 3rd party delivery service.  I understand how it's convenient and tempting to add costs, but at least be transparent. I would expect the delivery fee to go to the person delivering the food. Anything less is dishonest. Mario says he doesn't make the rules but he's taking advantage of his workers nonetheless.

O my goodness I don't eat pizza to often but this pizza put all other pizza to shame. It was sooooooo good, after my daughter Chicky order one a had to get my own. Next time it will be a larger one. I eat most of it with my granddaughter a had to get a pic. Of what was left. So good, so good.

The food speaks to whoever wants pizza. Can I say that every time I have called or had an adjustment, the staff has been really nice. They even sent me delivery without cost when the app messed up and told me its okay just tip the driver. And I did. And then the driver knocked on the door and said I had tipped him too much and made sure I knew the amount of cash I gave him. I'll order from them again but basically because the staff treats their customers like humans. And ill tip to that.

I placed an order to Jets through Uber Eats. The delivery driver completely messed up and gave me another persons order. I immediately called Jets to scold them for giving me someone’s food. I found out it wasn’t Jets’ fault, but the delivery driver through Uber Eats. Anyone who uses Uber Eats knows how frustrating it is to get through to an actual person. I called back Jets and let them know Uber was going to have to refund me for the mess up. The manager Carl was amazing!! He apologized profusely (even though it wasn’t Jets fault, it was Uber’s) and wanted to make the situation right. He offered to remake my order complimentary and have someone from their store deliver it to me. The whole staff was super kind in a situation where I was not. The food was delicious and they have incredible customer service! I highly recommend this Jets! :)

Pizza "slice" was a small square but it was absolutely delicious! So I really can't complain there. The employee offered for us to try it with their ranch. We did and loved that too so, per their sign, I said I'd buy a whole bottle. Then she took the side that we dipped our finger in, put it back behind the counter and gave us the whole bottle. Very weird. Like are you going to reuse that??? We told her we tried it too and she just was like "really" like yeah that's why I said I'd take a whole bottle. And the whole bottle was not open (you need scissors to cut the tip) so we ended up eating the pizza without ranch (booo) and walking home with a whole bottle, which I am very pleased to have in my fridge but super weird/confusing customer service. Probably won't return

FANtastic! With a clear emphasis on "fan", because I am certainly a fan. I originally had no intention of eating at Jet's pizza but it was recommended by a colleague and figured it was worth a try. I've worked at my fair share of pizza places and so I wasn't necessarily worried about being disappointed by the flavor, but after trying their Eugene pizza, cooked well-done, I was blown away. But that wasn't even the best part... What surprised me the most was the outstanding service that their employees provided. They were extremely welcoming and accommodating while we were waiting for our pizza which is honestly not something you can always expect from a pizza place. The overall experience was very pleasant and I can tell why people keep coming back. I would highly recommend this location.

I would like to give this restaurant no stars but the one star would come in to play because of the cashier and the cook. I ordered my pizza on grub hub at 11:45am and picked it up at 11:55 am. My order stated it wouldn't be ready until 12pm. But I like to get to restaurants earlier if I place a grubhub because its most likely done before the time they say. But anyways I get there and my pizza was not fresh, so I asked the cashier if they had any fresh pizza available. She asks the manager ( not sure of his name) and he was a complete jerk. He said they make there pizza fresh all the time but clearly the pizza I was handed was not fresh. So I asked the cook was it a big issue for me wanting my food that I paid for fresh and he said : NO and I do apologize about this matter. So the manager asked the cook once he went back to get me the fresh slices I preferred and the manager asked him was I ordering more ( as far as paying for another order). The cook handed me the pizza and told me to have a great day.  This is no good customer service at all on the managers part. I would not recommend this location just because of MANAGEMENT !!!!!!!!!!!!! YOU GUYS NEED A NEW MANAGER ...................THE POOR STAFF HAS TO DEAL WITH THIS MANAGER.........
